{"data":[{"type":"questionAttempts","id":"17645374","links":{"self":"https://app.emedici.com/api/questionAttempts/17645374"},"attributes":{"position":0,"marks":1,"score":0,"answeredAt":"2025-09-30T20:17:02+09:30","options":[1],"response":null,"finalizedAt":"2025-09-30T20:17:02+09:30"},"relationships":{"user":{"data":{"type":"users","id":"50098"}},"questionSession":{"data":null},"session":{"data":null},"question":{"data":{"type":"questions","id":"18108"}},"bookmark":{"data":null}}}],"included":[{"type":"questions","id":"18108","links":{"self":"https://app.emedici.com/api/questions/18108"},"relationships":{"item":{"data":{"type":"items","id":"10822"}},"activeRevision":{"data":{"type":"questionRevisions","id":"73547"}}}},{"type":"items","id":"10822","links":{"self":"https://app.emedici.com/api/items/10822"},"attributes":{"contentType":"question"},"relationships":{"content":{"data":{"type":"questions","id":"18108"}},"activeRevision":{"data":{"type":"itemRevisions","id":"59017"}},"tags":{"data":[{"type":"tags","id":"67"},{"type":"tags","id":"71"},{"type":"tags","id":"74"},{"type":"tags","id":"4931"},{"type":"tags","id":"4941"},{"type":"tags","id":"11256"}]},"contributions":{"data":[{"type":"contributions","id":"25189"},{"type":"contributions","id":"25192"}]}},"meta":{"canRevise":false,"canManage":false,"canDelete":false}},{"type":"questionRevisions","id":"73547","links":{"self":"https://app.emedici.com/api/questionRevisions/73547"},"attributes":{"stem":"\u003Cp\u003E\u003C/p\u003E","stemQuestion":"Which one of the following structures forms the inferior boundary of the quadrangular space?","responseType":"sba","marks":1,"options":["Surgical neck of humerus","Long head of triceps","Subscapularis","Teres minor","Teres major"],"correctOptions":[4],"correctResponses":null,"explanation":"\u003Cp\u003EThe quadrangular space is an anatomical region located in the shoulder, bordered by specific muscles and bone structures. It is clinically significant as it allows passage of the axillary nerve and the posterior circumflex humeral artery.\u003C/p\u003E\u003Cp\u003EThe \u003Cstrong\u003Eteres major\u003C/strong\u003E muscle forms the inferior boundary of the quadrangular space. This muscle is located on the posterior aspect of the shoulder and plays a role in the movement of the humerus.\u003C/p\u003E\u003Cp\u003EThe \u003Cstrong\u003Esurgical neck of the humerus\u003C/strong\u003E forms the lateral boundary of the quadrangular space, not the inferior boundary.\u003C/p\u003E\u003Cp\u003EThe \u003Cstrong\u003Elong head of the triceps\u003C/strong\u003E forms the medial boundary of the quadrangular space, not the inferior boundary.\u003C/p\u003E\u003Cp\u003EThe \u003Cstrong\u003Esubscapularis\u003C/strong\u003E muscle is located anteriorly and does not form a boundary of the quadrangular space.\u003C/p\u003E\u003Cp\u003EThe \u003Cstrong\u003Eteres minor\u003C/strong\u003E muscle forms the superior boundary of the quadrangular space, not the inferior boundary.\u003C/p\u003E","optionExplanations":["","","","",""],"learningPoints":["The quadrangular space is an anatomical region in the shoulder that allows passage of the axillary nerve and posterior circumflex humeral artery.","The boundaries of the quadrangular space are formed by specific muscles and bone structures.","The inferior boundary of the quadrangular space is formed by the teres major muscle."],"references":["West, S. G. (2019). Anatomy and physiology of the musculoskeletal system. Rheumatology Secrets E-Book: Rheumatology Secrets E-Book, 17","Miniato MA, Anand P, Varacallo M. Anatomy, Shoulder and Upper Limb, Shoulder. 2023 Jul 24. In: StatPearls [Internet]. Treasure Island (FL): StatPearls Publishing; 2024 Jan\u2013. PMID: 30725618","Hutson, M., \u0026 Ward, A. (Eds.). (2015). Oxford textbook of musculoskeletal medicine. Oxford University Press","McCausland C, Sawyer E, Eovaldi BJ, Varacallo M. Anatomy, Shoulder and Upper Limb, Shoulder Muscles. 2023 Aug 8. In: StatPearls [Internet]. Treasure Island (FL): StatPearls Publishing; 2024 Jan\u2013. PMID: 30521257","Paulsen, F., \u0026 Waschke, J. (Eds.). (2023). Sobotta Atlas of Anatomy, Vol. 1, English/Latin: General Anatomy and Musculoskeletal System (Vol. 1). Elsevier Health Sciences"]},"relationships":{"itemRevision":{"data":{"type":"itemRevisions","id":"59017"}},"question":{"data":{"type":"questions","id":"18108"}},"stemMedia":{"data":[]},"explanationMedia":{"data":[]}}},{"type":"itemRevisions","id":"59017","links":{"self":"https://app.emedici.com/api/itemRevisions/59017"},"attributes":{"createdAt":"2024-12-24T00:06:03+10:30","updatedAt":"2024-12-24T00:07:03+10:30"},"relationships":{"item":{"data":{"type":"items","id":"10822"}},"content":{"data":{"type":"questionRevisions","id":"73547"}}},"meta":{"canDelete":false}},{"type":"tags","id":"67","links":{"self":"https://app.emedici.com/api/tags/67"},"attributes":{"emoji":"","name":"Basic Science","synonyms":null,"description":null,"position":null,"createdAt":null,"updatedAt":null},"relationships":{"group":{"data":{"type":"tagGroups","id":"5"}},"heading":{"data":null}},"meta":{"itemCount":0}},{"type":"tags","id":"71","links":{"self":"https://app.emedici.com/api/tags/71"},"attributes":{"emoji":"","name":"Junior","synonyms":null,"description":"Suitable for a junior, pre-clinical medical student","position":0,"createdAt":null,"updatedAt":null},"relationships":{"group":{"data":{"type":"tagGroups","id":"6"}},"heading":{"data":null}},"meta":{"itemCount":0}},{"type":"tags","id":"74","links":{"self":"https://app.emedici.com/api/tags/74"},"attributes":{"emoji":"","name":"Level I","synonyms":null,"description":"Remember (identifying and retrieving information)","position":null,"createdAt":null,"updatedAt":null},"relationships":{"group":{"data":{"type":"tagGroups","id":"7"}},"heading":{"data":null}},"meta":{"itemCount":0}},{"type":"tags","id":"4931","links":{"self":"https://app.emedici.com/api/tags/4931"},"attributes":{"emoji":"\ud83e\uddb4","name":"Musculoske